      "id": "https://uofa.net/synth/validation/morrison-cou2-pressure-rise",
      "type": "ValidationResult",
      "name": "Pressure rise validation against FDA pump PIV data — MRL 5",
      "description": "CFD-predicted pressure rise compared against FDA benchmark experimental data at 5 operating points. Mean absolute error 8.3%; model under-predicts at high flow rates. Achieved credibility insufficient for MRL 5 absolute hemolysis claims."
    },
    {
      "id": "https://uofa.net/synth/validation/morrison-cou2-hemolysis-index",
      "type": "ValidationResult",
      "name": "Hemolysis index validation — absolute threshold assessment",
      "description": "Predicted normalized index of hemolysis (NIH) compared against in vitro measurements across 5 flow-speed combinations. Monte Carlo UQ (500 samples, Latin hypercube) propagated inlet velocity and viscosity uncertainties. 95th-percentile NIH prediction exceeds clinical threshold at two operating points, confirming insufficient model fidelity for Class III regulatory submission at MRL 5."
    }
